<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="173" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[159,809,408,561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis box="[197,254,409,432]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Notes</emphasis>
. – In Macaronesia, this lichenicolous fungus was previously only known from the 
<collectingRegion box="[516,592,440,464]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Azores</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="VAN DEN BOOM, P. P. G. &amp; D. ERTZ" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" pagination="295 - 301" part="46" refId="ref8575" refString="VAN DEN BOOM, P. P. G. &amp; D. ERTZ (2014). A new species of Micarea (Pilocarpaceae) from Madeira growing on Usnea. Lichenologist 46: 295 - 301." title="A new species of Micarea (Pilocarpaceae) from Madeira growing on Usnea" type="journal article" year="2014">VAN DEN BOOM &amp; ERTZ, 2014</bibRefCitation>
). It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Rabenh." authorityName="Rabenh." box="[559,761,472,496]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Abrothallaceae" genus="Abrothallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Abrothallales" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="usneae">
<emphasis box="[559,657,473,496]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">A. usneae</emphasis>
Rabenh.
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stein" box="[159,307,504,528]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Abrothallaceae" genus="Abrothallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Abrothallales" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chrysanthus">
<emphasis box="[159,307,504,528]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">A. chrysanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has ascospores of 8-10 × 3-4 µm and those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rabenh." box="[159,252,537,560]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Abrothallaceae" genus="Abrothallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Abrothallales" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="usneae">
<emphasis box="[159,176,537,560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[187,252,537,560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">usneae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are 14-18 × 5-7 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
